                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>2</p>\n            <p>more remarks. But will relate the unhappy events<lb/> which have just transpired</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You are perhaps aware there are about 70<lb/> Yechidim (voters) of\n                our congregation—among that<lb/> member there are 18 or 20 ultra Reformers,\n                about<lb/> the same number satisfied with the present<lb/> service &amp; the Balance\n                willing to go back to our<lb/> old mode of service—although not objectionable<lb/>\n                but fearing further charges.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">On the first day of the last<lb/>\n                <date>passover</date> the <persName>Rev G. Poznanski</persName> delivered an\n                English<lb/> discourse commemorative of the day &amp;c. and at the<lb/> close of the\n                discourse spoke of the <hi rend=\"underline\">useless</hi> observance<lb/> of the\n                second day, that the exact time was now<lb/> known &amp; this being known positively\n                by our almanacs<lb/> the observance therefore of the second day was<lb/> altogether\n                useless &amp; unnecessary. This annunciation<lb/> caused great excitement and\n                dissatisfaction<lb/> 8 or 9 persons (among whom was <persName>Mr Moses</persName>)\n                walked out<lb/> of the Synagogue. The matter was talked of<lb/> incessantly &amp;\n                discontent prevailed to an alarming<lb/> extent. The Trustees met &amp; a Preamble\n                &amp; Resolution<lb/> discountenancing the action of <persName>Mr\n                    Poznanski</persName> was<lb/> made &amp; carried at this meeting of the Board.\n                While in session<lb/> a letter was <sic>received</sic> from <persName>Mr\n                    Poznanski</persName> regretting<lb/> the excitement produced—claiming a\n                prerogative<lb/> that as the Trustees had requested him to</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g15tx51/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
