                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g15tx51/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">5</p>\n            <p><sic>Bretheren</sic> who were driven from the <del>old</del> Synagogue<lb/> applied\n                for Readmission with the privilege of a<lb/> vote. The opposite party heard of this\n                fact<lb/> for it was not done secretly, &amp; when 3 Trustees<lb/> applied to the\n                President <persName>Abraham Ottoler<add>?</add></persName> to<lb/> call a meeting\n                (in accordance with the Constitution) to<lb/> elect <del>a President</del> these\n                gentlemen, The President<lb/> refused to do so stating that a Petition had<lb/> been\n                presented to him signed by a constitutional<lb/> member to call a public\n                meeting—which he<lb/> must do &amp; that after said meeting he would call<lb/> the\n                Trustees together.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I must here observe that to call<lb/> a public meeting for general\n                purposes one third of<lb/> the Congregation petitionary to the President he is<lb/>\n                empowered to call it. But to <hi rend=\"underline\">alter the Constitution</hi><lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">one fourth</hi> of the congregation must petition to the<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">Board of Trustees</hi>, before whom the petition<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">must</hi> come for that purpose—when these gentl could have\n                been elected</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The meeting was called, The President stated<lb/> he called the\n                meeting in consequence of a Petition<lb/> received signed by 26 members and\n                would<lb/> be happy to hear any remarks &amp;c.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr. I N. Cardoza</persName> the editor rose<lb/> &amp;\n                proposed the following Resolutions or rather<lb/> the Basis of them I do not give\n                the<lb/> words.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g15tx51/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
